data.title: Great mexican food and service
data.text: Interesting place at it was originally a house so the set up is unique but it worked.  The fajitas were some of the best I have ever had. They were not sizzling when they came out like you normally get but the taste was amazing.  Just the right amount of onions and peppers as well.  The nacho chips and salsa were very fresh and tasty.  Our waitress was very attentive and over provided good service.  We will go back for sure. the prices were a little higher for mexican food but again, it was very good food.

data.title: Delicious
data.text: The food was amazing and the margaritas were heavenly. I liked that they offered different sizes and the Carne Asda Burrito I ordered was great! The meat was nice and tender and not chewy like I've had at other places.

data.title: Crazy workers crazy customers
data.text: From the waiter who was just hired that night to the ditzy waitress who couldn't remember who ordered what to the manager and wait staff who seemed to be indifferent of time and basic restaurant management. This place was horrible and seemed to bring in a lot of crazy obnoxious customers. Cheap booze and cheap food probably is the why for both crazy workers and customers.

data.title: BEST MARGARITA IN TOWN!
data.text: This is my wife and I favorite restaurant. We love the outside sitting. Old Victorian house convert into a restaurant. Excellent service.

data.title: Small portions for the $
data.text:
Ok, we heard about a New Mexican Reataurant  in Valley Junction. 
Thought we would check it out since we really enjoy a good Mexican meal. I thought we would check it out.
 Stopped by for lunch I had the chimichanga and my husband had the quesadilla. 
Each of the meals cost us $7.95 mine was a 3 inch deep that came with a small portion of ground beef in it, about a 1/4 cup of rice and 1/4 cup of beans.
We ordered water to drink.
Waitress could not wait to clear off our table immediately, we still had uneaten food on our table, she would stand over us like a hawk, how annoying, and this was before we even had our meal paid for.
 My husband made the comment that it seemed as if she was pulling the fork out of our mouth before we even finished our meal. 
I was in the middle of drinking my water and she asked if she could take the two glasses of water, to have completely cleared off the table, immediately on her way to swipe our credit card for the charges.  Before this, She tried to take our salsa and guacamole, which by the way cost us $2.95 for a fourth of a cup but I told her I was going to finish that $2.95 guacamole. 

 Really? 

I find it very irritating, I just want to sit at the table and relax after a meal and the waitress is pushing us out the door, and trying to remove the fork from our mouth before the meal is completed!

 There were one additional individual sitting in the restaurant so it was not as if she was busy!
